      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "As a consequence of highly fluctuating temperatures the snowpack consolidated. This applies in particular on steep sunny slopes at high altitude, and in all aspects at intermediate altitudes. The snowpack is fairly homogeneous and its surface has a melt-freeze crust. This applies in particular in the early morning. <br/> The weather conditions as the day progresses will give rise to rapid moistening of the snowpack. <br/> Below approximately 2400 m only a little snow is lying on south facing slopes."
      },
